odernize.";i:12;s:180:"And you all know that I rely 100 on my E-design clients photos to use on my blog so while I dont have TONS of examples I know youll find the images and info that I do have helpful.";i:13;s:145:"If you think molding of a particular shape would look good as a chair rail use it even if it is labeled for use as a baseboard or something else.";i:14;s:82:"But dont use crown molding because the pre-cut angle is unsuitable for chair rail.";i:15;s:79:"And even it is taller than the standard chair rail it doesnt dwarf the ceiling.";i:16;s:55:"Different bathrooms require different chair rail ideas.";i:17;s:104:"If you want to make the bathroom looks more modern choose wider and minimalist chair rail molding ideas.";i:18;s:82:"But for a classic look go for more intricate chair rail style with standard width.";i:19;s:71:"Unbranded 2-58-in x 12-ft Pine Primed Finger Joint Chair Rail Moulding.";i:20;s:82:"Chair rail moulding is often used around the wall of a room parallel to the floor.";i:21;s:90:"It is typically seen installed about one third the distance between the floor and ceiling.";i:22;s:90:"This is where the back of a chair would bump or strike the wall hence the name chair rail.";i:23;s:196:"A wooden picture rail can be stained and as with chair rails some people paint the walls up to and including the picture rail one color and make everything above that a different color says Dixon.";i:24;s:41:"I find that makes the ceiling look lower.";i:25;s:172:"The real purpose of a chair rail is to add visually pleasing architectural interest to your room so the walls dimensions are what should guide the placement of the molding.";i:26;s:99:"We can ignore lots of fancy math and simply estimate that the rail should hit about 13 up the wall.";i:27;s:124:"Chairs and chair rail may sound like they have a lot in common but the relationship is limited to their approximate heights.";i:28;s:70:"Chair rail is the most misused and abused molding in new houses today.";